article.headline: Long Beach St. 81, Green Bay 69
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Stephan Gilling scored 22 points to lead Long Beach State to an 81-69 victory over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Saturday. The 49ers (3-1) shot 63 percent from the field in the second half, making 15 of 24 shots, and were at 54 percent for the game. Larry Anderson scored 17 points and Eugene Phelps 15 for Long Beach State. Gilling was 6 of 14 from 3-point range and Anderson 9 of 10 from the free-throw line. Wisconsin-Green Bay (4-2) had five players in double figures. Randy Berry and Troy Cotton had 16 points each, Cordero Barkley 14, Rahmon Fletcher 11 and Bryquis Perine 10 for the Phoenix, who took 10 more shots than the 49ers but made three fewer and shot just 41 percent. Berry had a game-high 10 rebounds.
